author: Harry Fletcher
title: James Corden takes over as The Price Is Right's male model... and it does not go smoothly - US TV
text: James Corden has been up to his usual tricks again, this time causing mischief on the set of The Price Is Right.The late night star swapped presenting duties for modelling on the long-running game show, previewing the amazing prizes with mixed results.James Corden describes getting his OBE to Stephen ColbertThe presenter meets The Price Is Right's first male model James to learn a few tricks of the trade, and then naturally gets a tan to make himself ready for the show.But it doesn't all go smoothly - after looking around, Corden takes issue with the misleading nature of the prizes, and is sure to point out exactly what contestants can win, and what they can't.Corden soldiers on and ends up doing a fine job on the CBS show, but we still don't think he should give up his job at The Late Late Show any time soon.It's the latest entertaining skit from Corden and his team, after he tried his hand at baseball, performed a street musical, re-enacted the filmography of Matt Damon, went on a stakeout with Mel Brooks and staged a Taylor Swift soap opera.
